==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''oculus'', the eye.
===Noun===
'''oculus''' (''plural'' '''oculi''')

# A window that has an oval or circular shape.
# A circular [[hypaethral]] opening in the centre of a dome.
#:''One can glimpse the sky through the oculus of the Pantheon in Rome.''

